                <p>Varsity is among the most sought-after neighbourhoods in northwest Calgary. Developed in the 1960s and 1970s on a plateau situated north of the Bow River valley, Varsity is home to beautiful parks, local schools, and a golf course. The Greater Varsity neighbourhood consists of the community of Varsity Estates in addition to Varsity Village and Varsity Acres.</p>
                <p>Varsity is nestled just south west of Crowchild Trail, east of the Bow River, and north of 32nd Avenue NW. The neighbourhoods of Silver Springs and Bowness are on its west, while the University of Calgary and Montgomery campuses are on the southern side. The University of Calgary Research Park is situated in the eastern part of Varsity.</p>
                <p>Parks, malls, bars, restaurants, and entertainment are easy to find in the community. Those seeking adventure will love the outdoors and adventure spots located in Varsity. If you are considering a move to Varsity, you will love the family-friendly feel and the tons of options to explore in the local area.</p>
