                <div>
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Golf &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Varsity is home to Silver Springs Golf & Country Club, which is located just 15 minutes away from downtown Calgary. It has more than 300 acres of valleys and hills with gradual changes in elevation. If you want to plan a wedding or large business events in an intimate setting, Silver Springs is a great option for you.</p>
                    <p>Another place that golf enthusiasts will love is the Valley Ridge Golf Club. It is situated in the Bow River Valley and is about 15 minutes away from downtown Calgary. You can host special events like weddings and Christmas and corporate events here. For those looking to try out their golfing skills, you can sign up for golf courses and membership at Valley Ridge.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks &amp; Recreation &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>There are various parks and recreational facilities in Varsity. Whether you want to go for a run in a calming place or use an exercise facility for a more private workout, you will not run out of options. You can find a playground on 49 St. NW, which is farthest from the neighbourhood of all the other parks.</p>
                    <p>If you are looking for a nearer place, you can visit Varsity Estates Park, which has a dog park, a playground, and trails. You might also visit the playground at Varsity Green NW. If you are willing to go a bit farther, you will find Varsity Acres Park, which has a sports field, a playground, a trail, and a ball diamond. Those who are more athletic would certainly enjoy working out in this park.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid_12" style="margin-top: 3rem;">
            <div class="x6">
                <div>
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Restaurants and bars &mdash;</h3>
                    Boston Pizza, Matador Pizza, and Varsity Pizza & Subs are popular in the neighbourhood for offering Italian dining, delivery, and takeout menu options. You can also visit Peking Garden Calgary, Cuty Vietnamese Kitchen, and Vietnamese Chop Chop for Asian food. If you are in a rush and want to grab some sandwiches and coffee, try Fresh Blend Coffee & Sandwich Bar and CHACHI’S. Some well-known bars in the neighbourhood of Varsity include The Canadian Brewhouse, Jamesons Pub, The Den, and Last Defence Lounge.
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">University of Calgary &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>This community is just a short drive away from the University of Calgary making it a popular location for university staff and students alike. This provides other opportunities for rental properties, as well as those looking to have their older children attend post-secondary school while still living at home. </p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Convenience &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Varsity is home to a variety of retail opportunities including a Safeway located inside Market mall. If you are looking for a one stop shopping experience head over to Northland Village where you will find a large Walmart store. Need a cup of coffee and some donuts after the heavy workout? Head over to Starbucks after you have finished working out at the GoodLife Fitness gymnasium.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
