        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>In 2016, there were 12,800 people living in private households in Varsity, of which 29% were immigrants. Those in the age group of 15-64 years made up about 66% of this population.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>Homes of different styles are available for purchase to buyers looking to invest in a property in Varsity. There are duplexes, homes with an attached garage, townhomes, and so forth. The architectural styles of these homes are traditional, ranch, craftsman, prairie, cottage, farmhouse, and modern. Whether you are a couple looking to start a new life or need a big space for a growing family, Varsity has you covered with its ample real estate offerings.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Developer/ Builder History</h3>
            <p>Carma Developers developed Varsity Village in the late 1960s and 1970s. The real estate development here is part of the overall development of the greater Varsity community, which began with the construction of single-family homes. Today, clusters of low-rise, apartment-style condominiums can be seen to the west of Market Mall, in addition to various other structural styles of homes.</p>
            <p>Varsity was created in a convenient location that is only a few minutes away from shopping malls, schools, recreational areas, parks, and more. Interested buyers can schedule a tour of homes for sale by getting in touch with one of our area experts.</p>
        </div>
